# Invite flow ‚Äî commander, Ashed member, HQ user, HQ member

**Do not conflate four different things.** The web invite path touches all of them; mixing layers caused production bugs (wrong `hq_member_links` row, 404 on magic-link retry).

## Four entities (use precise terms in code and copy)

| Concept | Storage | Primary key / scope | Answers |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **In-game commander** | Last War API (live lookup by UID) | Player UID (12‚Äì16 digits; suffix is state server number) | ‚ÄúWhat does the **game server** call this player **right now**?‚Äù |
| **Ashed roster member** | `alliance_members` (+ live Ashed API when local empty) | `ashed_member_id` per `alliance_id` | ‚ÄúWho is on **our alliance roster** in HQ/Ashed?‚Äù (`current_name`, `previous_names_json`) |
| **HQ user** | `hq_users` + Auth.js session | `hq_users.id` | ‚ÄúWho signed into Alliance HQ?‚Äù (email / magic link) |
| **HQ member (RBAC)** | `alliance_memberships` | `(alliance_id, hq_user_id)` ‚Üí role | ‚ÄúWhat **permissions** does this HQ user have in this alliance?‚Äù (owner, officer, member, ‚Ä¶) |

**Fifth binding row (web only):** `hq_member_links` maps **`hq_user_id` ‚Üí `ashed_member_id`** within one alliance, plus stored `game_uid` and display name snapshot. This is **not** RBAC and **not** created by roster sync alone.

| Binding | Table | Unique constraints | Created when |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| HQ user ‚Üî roster character | `hq_member_links` | one user per alliance; one Ashed member per alliance | Successful **member-link** submit (`/api/member-link`) |
| HQ user ‚Üî alliance role | `alliance_memberships` | one membership per user per alliance | **Invite accept** (`acceptHqInvite`) ‚Äî before member link |
| Roster mirror | `alliance_members` | one row per `ashed_member_id` per alliance | Ashed sync / import ‚Äî **not** on invite accept |

Discord bot uses **`discord_member_links`** (Discord user ‚Üî commander) ‚Äî parallel idea, different table. See [`.cursor/rules/discord-identity-auth-layers.mdc`](discord-identity-auth-layers.mdc).

## Three name authorities (never substitute one for another)

```
User types name          Last War UID lookup          HQ roster (alliance_members)
     ‚îÇ                          ‚îÇ                              ‚îÇ
     ‚îÇ   must match             ‚îÇ   gameUserName               ‚îÇ   current_name or
     ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î§   (authoritative for         ‚îÇ   previous_names only
                                ‚îÇ    identity)                   ‚îÇ
                                ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ exact match ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫‚îÇ
