```

| Source | Trust level | Used for |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Last War API** (`player-lookup`, UID) | **Identity** ‚Äî proves UID owns `gameUserName` | Gate: reported name must match lookup; roster match uses **`gameUserName`**, not fuzzy typed text |
| **`alliance_members`** | **Alliance roster snapshot** ‚Äî may lag renames | Exact match only on `current_name` + `previous_names` (`findExactMemberByName`) |
| **User-typed name** | Untrusted until it matches Last War | Walkthrough when mismatch; never fuzzy-link roster from typed string alone |

**Pitfall (Lil Belly / Mr BELLY):** UID proved ‚ÄúLil Belly‚Äù but roster still showed ‚ÄúStitch‚Äù. **Fuzzy** matching `"lil belly"` ‚Üí `"Mr BELLY"` linked the wrong `ashed_member_id`. **Fix:** no fuzzy pick on member-link; roster miss + officer path when game name ‚âÝ any exact roster name.

**Do not** reuse `findFuzzyMemberCandidates` / video OCR fuzzy helpers for invite or member-link flows. Fuzzy remains for **video OCR** only (`member-matcher.ts`).

## Web invite ‚Üí onboard sequence

```
Admin invite (email / protected link)
    ‚Üí GET /invite/[token]  (preview; needs Auth.js to accept)
    ‚Üí POST /invite/[token]/accept
         creates alliance_memberships (RBAC from invite role)
         does NOT create hq_member_links
    ‚Üí redirect /onboard?next=‚Ä¶
    ‚Üí MemberLinkOnboardingWizard
         POST /api/member-link  (name + UID)
         creates hq_member_links on exact roster match
    ‚Üí redirect next (e.g. /members, /trains)
```

**Gates on `(app)` layout** (native alliance):

| Gate | Checks | Independent of |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `hasAppAccess` | invite / join code / maintainer | member link |
| `requiresMemberLink` | `hq_member_links` for current alliance | RBAC role |
| `requiresAshedVerification` | always false for new privileged-link policy | member link |

**Auth for accept:** invite accept API requires **both** `alliance_hq_session` and `authjs.session-token` (see `e2e/fixtures/auth.ts`). Magic links are **single-use** ‚Äî expired/used links hit `/auth/error` (not 404).

## Member-link algorithm invariants (`processLinkCommand`)

Implement and preserve in tests (`src/lib/vr/link-command.test.ts`):

1. UID lookup must succeed (`lookup.ok`).
2. `namesMatch(reportedName, gameUserName)` ‚Äî normalized equality; else walkthrough, no link.
3. `findExactMemberByName(members, gameUserName)` ‚Äî **exact** on current + previous names only.
4. If exact row found and not already linked ‚Üí `linkTarget` with that `ashed_member_id` and submitted `game_uid`.
5. If no exact row ‚Üí **`needsOfficerAttention`** / roster miss ‚Äî explain game name vs stale roster; **no candidate picker**.
6. `memberTaken` if `ashed_member_id` already has `hq_member_links` for another user.

**Roster load:** `loadAllianceMembersForMemberLink` ‚Äî prefer local `alliance_members`, then live Ashed. Audit `rosterSource` on submit failures.

## RBAC vs character link (common design mistakes)

| Mistake | Why it‚Äôs wrong |
| --- | --- |
| Grant app access from member link alone | RBAC comes from **invite** / `alliance_memberships`; link only binds character |
| Require Ashed connect before member link (web) | Privileged roles get RBAC from invite; Ashed is optional (embeds/sync) |
| Infer commander from session `userLabel` / Ashed JWT display name | Link requires explicit UID + roster `ashed_member_id` |
| Write `hq_member_links` during roster sync | Sync writes `alliance_members` only; link is user-initiated |
| Use fuzzy / Levenshtein to ‚Äúhelp‚Äù renamed players | Substring similarity links wrong people; use roster miss + officer refresh |
| Match roster on **typed** name when UID lookup disagrees | UID path already verified game name ‚Äî roster must match **that** string |
| One HQ user ‚Üí multiple characters per alliance | `hq_member_links` is 1:1 per `(alliance_id, hq_user_id)` today |

## Rename and staleness

- **Game renames** (Stitch ‚Üí Lil Belly) update Last War immediately; **`alliance_members.current_name`** updates on next Ashed/sync refresh.
- Until roster catches up, correct UX is **roster miss** (with `rosterMissVerified` copy), not guessing.
- **`previous_names_json`** may bridge renames if Ashed/history captured old name ‚Äî still **exact** match only.
- Officer recovery: refresh roster from Ashed, or admin ops on `hq_member_links` (delete wrong row, user re-links).

## Negative cases to test

| Scenario | Expected |
| --- | --- |
| UID valid, game name ‚âÝ roster | Roster miss; no `hq_member_links` |
| Similar roster names (shared substring) | No link to wrong member |
| Invite accept without sign-in | 401 / redirect to `/auth` with `callbackUrl` back to invite |
| Reused magic link after logout | `/auth/error?error=Verification`, CTA for new link |
| Accept invite then skip onboard | `(app)` redirects to `/onboard` until linked |
| Link succeeds | `hq_member_links.game_uid` = submitted UID; `ashed_member_id` = matched roster row |

Update `e2e/invite-roles.spec.ts`, `e2e/onboard-member-link.spec.ts`, and unit tests when changing any step above.

